# Inspect the Data

# Data Wrangling
NHANES2 <-
  NHANES %>%
  select(AgeDecade, BMI_WHO, Diabetes) %>%
  arrange(AgeDecade)
NHANES2Clean <-
  NHANES2[- c(1:2766), ]
NHANES2Plot <-
  mosaicplot(~ AgeDecade + BMI_WHO + Diabetes, data = NHANES2, shade = TRUE, xlab = "AgeDecade")

part A

Inspect the data

babynames

Data wrangling

BabynamesDist <- make_babynames_dist()

com_fem <-

BabynamesDist %>% filter(sex == F) %>% group_by(name) %>% summarise( N = n(), est_num_alive = sum(est_alive_today), q1_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.25), median_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.5), q3_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.75)) %>% arrange(desc(est_num_alive)) %>% head(25)

w_plot <- ggplot(data = com_fem, aes(x = reorder(name, -median_age), y = median_age)) + xlab(NULL) + ylab(Age (in years)) + ggtitle(Median ages for females with the 25 most common names)

w_plot <- w_plot + geom_linerange(aes(ymin = q1_age, ymax = q3_age), color = #f3d478, size = 10, alpha = 0.8)

w_plot <- w_plot + geom_point(fill = #ed3324, colour = white, size = 4, shape = 21)

w_plot + geom_point(aes(y = 55, x = 24), fill = #ed3324, colour = white, size = 4, shape = 21) + geom_text(aes(y = 58, x = 24, label = median)) + geom_text(aes(y = 26, x = 16, label = 25th)) + geom_text(aes(y = 51, x = 16, label = 75th percentile)) + geom_point(aes(y = 24, x = 16), shape = 17) + geom_point(aes(y = 56, x = 16), shape = 17) + coord_flip()

# part B
# Inspect the data
babynames
# Data wrangling
BabynamesDist <- make_babynames_dist()
com_fem <- 
  BabynamesDist %>% 
  filter(sex == "F", est_alive_today > 0) %>% #Add "est_alive_today > 0" to get rid of NA error
  group_by(name) %>% 
  summarise( 
    N = n(), 
    est_num_alive = sum(est_alive_today), 
    q1_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.25),
    median_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.5),
    q3_age = wtd.quantile(age_today, est_alive_today, probs = 0.75)) %>%
arrange(desc(est_num_alive)) %>%
  head(25)
w_plot <-
  ggplot(data = com_fem,
         aes(x = reorder(name, -median_age), y = median_age)) +
  xlab(NULL) +
  ylab("Age (in years)") +
  labs(title = "Median ages for females with the 25 most common names", # Changed "ggtitle"" function to "labs" in order to add subtitle and caption
       subtitle = "Among Americans to be alive as of Jan. 1, 2014",
       caption = "Source: Social Security Administration")
w_plot <-
  w_plot +
  geom_linerange(aes(ymin = q1_age, ymax = q3_age), color = "#f3d478", size = 10, alpha = 0.8)
w_plot <-
  w_plot +
  geom_point(fill = "#ed3324", colour = "white", size = 4, shape = 21)
w_plot +
  geom_point(aes(y = 55, x = 24), fill = "#ed3324", colour = "white", size = 4, shape = 21) +
  geom_text(aes(y = 58, x = 24, label = "median")) +
  geom_text(aes(y = 26, x = 16, label = "25th")) +
  geom_text(aes(y = 51, x = 16, label = "75th percentile")) +
  geom_point(aes(y = 24, x = 16), shape = 17) +
  geom_point(aes(y = 56, x = 16), shape = 17) +
  ylim(15, 75) + # Added y limit
  coord_flip()

  • Added est_alive_today > 0 to get rid of NA error
  • Changed ggtitle" function to labs in order to add subtitle and caption
  • Added y limit
